Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine brown-buff. Circular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Apatourios. Trimmed. Maiuri, ASA 4-5 (1921-2) p. 269 publishes a jar from Villanova with two stamps, one from the same die; see also Finkielsztein 2001, 184, note 81. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0062.24.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0527)
